reviews.review_text: grate tape from the west wow! nice job on gaining the right real estate to tape this.the 700's are always welcome.thanks for the hook

Don't Overlook This One This AUD has the warmest sound of the Spokane tapes here. Clear and present, with just enough live ambience. Beautiful. The Dead visited Spokane just this once, but they sure made it count. Everything sparkles. Even the Cowboy Bob covers are played with conviction. Anchorage seems to get the most attention, but if you're following this Northwest run, or just digging into 1980 in general, don't miss this one.

So it appears you have no clue what you are talking about. It one of the best sounding tapes I made and you are a clueless idiot.

A+ performance and recording This recording is absolutely stellar. The performance is too. Vocals and guitars are crystal clear, and Jerry and the rest of the band are completely ON. 'Nuff said. Very special tape.
